      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Understanding Nanonets OCR S and Its Cost Model"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Nanonets OCR S is a specialized model designed for high-accuracy text extraction from images and documents, optimized for production API use. Its cost model is primarily usage-based, charging per API call with factors like image resolution and processing complexity influencing the final price. Unlike flat-rate services, this allows for scalability but requires careful monitoring to prevent cost creep during peak loads."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The model's efficiency in handling varied document types—from invoices to handwritten notes—makes it a cost-effective choice for teams needing reliable OCR without sacrificing speed. Key cost drivers include the number of API requests, image dimensions (as larger images may incur higher fees), and any additional post-processing features enabled. Understanding these variables is the first step toward predictable spending."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Cost Breakdown: Pricing Tiers and Usage Metrics"
