            "type": "text",
            "text": "Performance metrics directly influence cost efficiency; higher accuracy models often come with increased latency and price. Nanonets OCR S maintains an average latency of 200-500ms per image for standard resolutions, which balances speed and cost for most production workloads. However, opting for enhanced accuracy modes can increase latency to 800ms and raise costs by 20-30%, so evaluate based on your error tolerance."
